modified Connect Four; two player game where:
- board with 7 x 7 slots (7 per row, 7 per column)
- each player assigned a colour (red or blue)
- red starts, alternating turns
- each player drops coloured token into column, token drops to lowest slot in column (if no slots available, doesn't drop)
- when player has four coloured tokens in a row (vertically, horizontally, or diagonally), receives one point
- when all slots filled, player with most points wins (if equal, tie)
